^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The rule of 20 is recommended by Bergen to determine if you have an opening hand. You add your raw HCP to the length of your 2 longest suits. If the total is 20 or more, you should open the hand. For example, an 11 point 5-4-2-2 hand is an opener (11 + 9 = 20), as is a 12 point 4-4-3-2 hand (12 + 8 = 20).|
